laboratory_examinations.findings: The appendix is hyperemic, fluid-filled and dilated measuring up to 11 mm in diameter with periappendiceal fluid and inflammation. A hypodensity in the left lobe of the liver measuring 6 mm, likely a simple cyst. A 2.5 x 1.5 x 2.7 cm lesion in the right adrenal gland. Pelvic free fluid noted.
